President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Mississippi due to the impact of Hurricane Nate from October 6 to October 10, 2017. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in the counties of George, Greene, Harrison, and Jackson. Additionally, federal funding will be provided for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Manny J. Toro has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made in the future if requested by the state and justified by damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.